main event: A civilian reported a UFO sighting in Superior, Wisconsin on 23 August 1965, observing a green object for one hour.
interesting points: The object was observed for one hour with no sound, exhaust, or trail., The object disappeared over the horizon after being initially spotted to the north., The sighting was concluded to be possibly a star based on the description and elevation., The object was described as having a penny-sized appearance at arm's length with green coloration and a red ring around it., Officials regarded the evidence as insufficient for evaluation, requesting further information.
sighted object: one green object with no discernible features
